<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<recipe>
    <name>Yellow Chicken Curry With Peppercons (KAENG KARII KAI)</name>
    <indexCharacter>Y</indexCharacter>
    <notes>FRESH PEPPERCORNS HAVE A FRAGRANT, PUNGENT QUALITY THAT LIFTS THE FLAVOR OF ANY CURRY IN WHICH THEY ARE USED. YOU SHOULD BEWARE OF EATING A WHOLE SPRIG IN ONE GO THOUGH AS, JUST LIKE THE PEPPER THEY BECOME, THEY ARE EXTREMELY HOT.</notes>
    <servings>4</servings>
    <instructions>PUT the coconut cream in a wok or saucepan and
simmer over a medium heat for about 5 minutes,
or until the cream separates and a layer of oil
forms on the surface. Stir the cream if it starts to
brown around the edges.

ADD the curry paste, stir well to combine and
cook until fragrant. Add the fish sauce, palm sugar
and turmeric and stir well. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes,
stirring occasionally, until the mixture darkens.

ADD the chicken to the pan and stir to coat all
the pieces evenly in the spice mixture. Cook
over a medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring
occasionally and adding the coconut milk a
tablespoon at a time to incorporate. Add the
bamboo shoots, peppercorns, lime and basil
leaves and cook for another 5 minutes.</instructions>
